<h3>Re: [SOLVED] Download Security</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>Simply the sha512 ans sha256 hashes are already with the iso. B) Even tor is not secure. So even if you can switch anytime to https, if you want the maximum level of security, I can send the iso burned to you via mail (yes the old and sweet mail lol) on dvd-r, as others do this, signed with my gpg key (or the fsfe one on me fellowship card).</p><p>***Note***&#160; &#160;And by the way if you do read the info out there,&#160; Linux Mint got Hacked. SO before seriously writing a true novel on our distribution we need to alleviate all possibilities or errors and ( low security ) doubts.&#160; &#160;This distribution has made it to the top 2017 list and it was not because its some little unpopular piece.&#160; So with that, if there is anything else I am able to help you with, please do not hesitate to contact me directly.</p>
</div>
